### Purpose
Xattrs through a real FUSE mount. Tests use `os.getxattr`/`os.setxattr`/`os.listxattr`/`os.removexattr` — the standard libc interface. Where available, also the `getfattr`/`setfattr` CLI tools from `attr` package.

All tests `<!-- trace: skipped -->` — syscall boundary.

### Implementation Notes

```python
import errno
import os
import shutil
import subprocess
import pytest

pytestmark = pytest.mark.fuse

HAS_SETFATTR = shutil.which("setfattr") is not None
```

---

## `test_fuse_xattr_set_get(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fxattr-2 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
path = mount / "f"
path.touch()

os.setxattr(path, "user.tag", b"hello")
assert os.getxattr(path, "user.tag") == b"hello"
```

---

## `test_fuse_xattr_list(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fxattr-3 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
path = mount / "f"
path.touch()

os.setxattr(path, "user.a", b"1")
os.setxattr(path, "user.b", b"2")
# os.listxattr returns a list of str names.
names = sorted(os.listxattr(path))
assert names == ["user.a", "user.b"]
```

---

## `test_fuse_xattr_remove(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fxattr-4 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
path = mount / "f"
path.touch()

os.setxattr(path, "user.tag", b"v")
os.removexattr(path, "user.tag")

with pytest.raises(OSError) as e:
    os.getxattr(path, "user.tag")
assert e.value.errno in (errno.ENODATA, errno.ENOATTR)
```

---

