## `test_fuse_setfattr_cli_round_trip(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fxattr-8 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary + external tool -->

### Postconditions

```python
if not HAS_SETFATTR:
    pytest.skip("setfattr not installed")

path = mount / "f"
path.touch()

subprocess.run(["setfattr", "-n", "user.tag", "-v", "cli-value", str(path)],
               check=True)
out = subprocess.run(["getfattr", "-n", "user.tag", "--only-values", str(path)],
                     check=True, capture_output=True)
assert out.stdout == b"cli-value"
```

